HEADWORD: Associator
<hw>As*so"ci*a`tor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An associate;
a confederate or partner in any scheme.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How Pennsylvania's air agrees with Quakers,⟦br⟧
And Carolina's with <qex>associators</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assoil</ent>⟦br⟧
